Become su and do the following:

step1: Copy rpm link from artifactory and wget to download 

step2: mkdir an install directory for the current rpms you want to install(basic housekeeping stuff)

step3: wget -c XXXX.rpm --no-check-certificate

step4: yum install XXXX.rpm

step5: repeat for dependencies until you have them satisfied and have the final pkg you want installed.

make sure you have dependencies in correct order.
